gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 120, Pistons 109
gameRecap.excerpt: Stephen Curry recorded 34 points and four assists for the Warriors as they defeated the Pistons, 120-109. Chris Paul added a season-high 17 points, along with five rebounds, and six assists for the Warriors in the victory, while Ausar Thompson tallied 16 points, seven rebounds, and four steals for the Pistons in the losing effort. The Warriors improve to 6-2 on the season, while the Pistons fall to 2-6.
